The paper proposes a new deep architecture for graphical model inference and learning, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. Specifically, the paper discusses learning algorithms based on backpropagation and EM, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve image completion, which is a task in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions potential connections to the architecture of the cortex, which is relevant to neuroscience and neural engineering (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the representation of marginals in graphical models, which is relevant to natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
